    "details": "# Problem Description\n\nWhile processing Link Control Protocol (LCP) configuration options\nreceived from the remote host, sppp(4) fails to correctly validate\noption lengths. This may result in data being read or written beyond the\nallocated kernel memory buffer.\n\n# Impact\n\nAn attacker able to send LCP packets, including the remote end of a\nsppp(4) connection, can cause the FreeBSD kernel to panic. Such an\nattacker may also be able to obtain sensitive information or gain\nelevated privileges.\n\n# Workaround\n\nNo workaround is available, but systems which do not use sppp(4) are not\nvulnerable.\n",
